            <title>[JCR-1708] Impossible to import a string containing _x0020_  with Session.importXml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1708</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The importXml uses the ValueHelper.serialize methods. The option &amp;quot;decodeBlanks&amp;quot; does a simple string replace which replaces _x0020_ in spaces (line 695 and 793). This option is always set to true unless the imported data is binary. See: BufferedStringValue and StringValue getValue methods.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The result is that it is now impossible to import a string with _x0020_ in it, because it gets translated in a space. The simple solution would be to just turn off the declodeBlanks option, but I&amp;#39;m not sure why it was added in the first place. Another option would be to use real encoding instead of a replace like the o.a.j.util.ISO9075.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
